node.text:
To celebrate @elijahcraig Old-Fashioned Week, Lynnette Marrero (@drinksat6), bar director of Llama San (@llamasannyc), Llama Inn (@llamainnnyc) and Wonderbar (@wonderbarbeacon), shares how to make her Three Bites of the Apple, an Old-Fashioned inspired by autumn in the Hudson Valley. ⁠
Get the recipe at punchdrink.com and learn more about how you can raise an Elijah Craig Bourbon Old-Fashioned to support the bar community at OldFashionedWeek.com.
#punchpartner @elijahcraig #oldfashionedweek @rwcfusa 
#oldfashioned #cocktail #bartender

Welcome to a special charity episode of “Tip Your Bartender” all about Aperitivo to benefit @rwcfusa! This episode supports industry workers in need by raising funds for @rwcfusa. You can make a contribution by going to the link in our profile, or heading over to @rwcfusa. To date, the Bacardi family of brands has contributed over $150,000 to aid in @rwcfusa’s ongoing relief efforts. @martinirossius will continue their support with a donation following this segment. #raiseyourspirits #drinkpunchtyb

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on September 08, 2021. May be an image of drink and text that says 'The Martini's Long Lost Sibling Steps Out The Turf Club has finally found a band of devotees. story: ROBERT SIMONSON photo: LIZZIE MUNRO'.

node.text: The Martini has enjoyed the spotlight for so long, nearly every one of the drink’s many variations has enjoyed its moment in the sun. But the Turf Club, a mixture of gin, vermouth, maraschino liqueur, absinthe and orange bitters, which predates the Martini and is just as old as the Martinez, has been patiently waiting its turn. The wait may soon be over. A few select, but prominent, bars have taken up the 1880s relic as their own, including the reborn Brooklyn's @gage.and.tollner, Miami's @surfclubrestaurant and @holywatersf in San Francisco. All three establishments have been pleasantly surprised that their beloved obscure drink has also become a favorite with their customers. Head to the link in our profile for more from @robertosimonson on why it's time to join the Turf Club. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text:
There is no one way to make a spritz. Increasingly, bartenders are putting local, seasonal and even personal spins on Italy’s easy-drinking aperitivo, reaching for bottles that lend complexity and dimension to the simple template. Head to the link in our profile where three bartenders in New York, Miami and Las Vegas share their elevated takes on the classic template using the subtle bergamot, citrus and herbal notes of Italicus Rosolio di Bergamotto.⁠
#punchpartner @italicusrdb #italicus #aperitivo⁠
📷: @lizzieamunro⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on September 07, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: Inspired by the daiquiri Hemingway famously drank at El Floridita, @orestesmixdrinks'a The Smoke Also Rises is his take on the Papa Doble. His rendition changes little from the rum-grapefruit-maraschino combination of the original, but a half-ounce of Amaro Sfumato leads to a smokier variation that feels as timeless as the Cuban classic. Head to the link in our profile for the recipe. #drinkpunch 📷: @angiewebbphoto

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on September 07, 2021. May be an image of food, drink and indoor.

node.text: Hold on to summer with @adambernbach's Appenini Spritz. A luscious, bitter take on a Negroni Sbagliato, Bernbach switches the traditional sweet vermouth element for Cocchi’s Barolo Chinato and matches it to the wine-based red bitter Cappelletti. Borrowing its name from the chain of mountains that run the length of peninsular Italy, the Appenines, it's a fresh take on the Milanese classic. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on September 06, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: The Espresso Martini was boldly declared to be the “drink of the summer” by numerous media outlets earlier this year. But did the boozy, caffeinated cocktail live up to the projected hype? 🤔 If you haven’t had one yet, there’s still time. Head to the link in our profile for @patrickftwinston’s perfected take, which gets an unexpected hit of vanilla that takes the decadent ‘80s-era classic into the modern age. #drinkpunch 📷: @ericmedsker

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on September 05, 2021. May be an image of drink and indoor.

node.text:
When you want something spicy and agave-based, but you're looking for something a little more interesting than a spicy Margarita, make @thepastrywar's "Spicy With Tequila." A mix of tequila, green Chartreuse, lime juice, agave nectar, mint and a house-made habanero tincture, @bobby_heugel’s response to the common request is undoubtedly more challenging than a spicy Margarita, with the cool sensation of mint contrasting sharply with the heat of the chile, and the unexpected herbaceousness of Chartreuse. Get the recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro⁠

node.text: If it’s not a bright pink drink, is it still a watermelon cocktail? @orlandofranklin, bar director at Brooklyn’s Nightmoves, subverts expectations by clarifying watermelon juice to a transparent, pale-pink state for his Watermelon Pastis. While McCray uses a centrifuge, he recognizes that it’s a piece of equipment few have at home. The drink works with non-clarified juice too, he notes, and will appear “milky pink” once added to the pastis. Get the recipe for this simple, sophisticated take on the watermelon cocktail via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro ⁠

node.text: "The Gin Rickey represents Washington, D.C., at its core,” says Andra “AJ” Johnson (@whiteplatesblackfaces). “It’s truly Numero Uno in this region.” At its core, the highball is a simple combination of gin, lime and seltzer, but there are countless variations, from different styles of gin and toppers to riffs made with everything from aquavit to fino sherry. “You should have fun with Gin Rickeys, because they’re so adaptable,” says Johnson. “To me, the best way to do that is with different syrups, like lavender or citrus.” Head to the link in our profile for more on how Johnson has mastered the city’s official cocktail and get the recipe for her bright, floral, earthy take on it. #drinkpunch 📷: @reema_desai

node.text: The watermelon cocktail is all grown up. Forget the watermelon ’tinis of the late ’90s, the latest generation of pink drinks is anything but basic. Today, bartenders are giving the crowd-pleasing fruit a clever, sophisticated edge by enhancing it with saline or spice, and marrying it with unexpected spirits. From fino sherry to curry bitters, the new crop of watermelon cocktails are summery and refreshing, but have an unexpected layer of intrigue. Head to the link in our profile for four sun-soaked pink drinks perfect for late summer, including @drinksat6's Melancholia (pisco, watermelon, rosé, habanero), pictured above. 🍉 #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: “The Boogie Nights really sells itself once it hits the table. It’s a chain reaction,” says @thaidiner’s Vince Ott. Consider the multi-colored frozen drink a Margarita turned up to an 11. Ott jazzes up the tequila base with maraschino liqueur, dragon fruit purée and pops of citrus from a makrut lime syrup and makrut lime sugar–salt rim. An unexpected spritz of green Chartreuse adds an herbaceous finish to the drink, which is garnished with a pineapple frond and cheeky paper umbrella. If you can't make it to New York's Thai Diner, head to the link in our profile for the recipe. #drinkpunch 📷: @brianabalducciphoto
